ciscoSibuStackableDualSpeedHubMIB.name: ciscoSibuStackableDualSpeedHubMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoSibuStackableDualSpeedHubMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-sibu@cisco.com
ciscoSibuStackableDualSpeedHubMIB.description: The MIB module that extends the REPEATER-MIB to manage CISCO low end stackable repeater products. For the purpose of this mib, a hub is a repeater group and stack is collection of one or more hubs interconnected via stack bus connectors.

HubNumber.name: HubNumber
HubNumber.description: Represents the hub number that the system supports for stacking. The hub number represents the order in which a hub is stacked relative to other members of the stack. Lowest hub number represents the top member of the stack. This is also the number used in the command line interface.

cssSystemLinkTraps.name: cssSystemLinkTraps
cssSystemLinkTraps.description: Indicates whether the stack is permitted to generate linkUp/linkDown traps for both repeater port and switch module's port. The stack provides only a single global control of link traps in contrast to per interface control provided by IF-MIB. The value of all instances ifLinkUpDownTrapEnable is set to TRUE (FALSE) if this object is set to enabled (disabled). The object ifLinkUpDownTrapEnable is read-only. A linkUp/linkDown trap is generated whenever a port's link STATUS or administrative status changes.

cssGroupTable.name: cssGroupTable
cssGroupTable.description: A list of member hubs in the stack.

cssGroupEntry.name: cssGroupEntry
cssGroupEntry.description: Configuration parameters for an individual hub. An entry is created by default for the master unit in the stack. A entry is created (removed) when a hub is connected to (removed from) the stack.

cssGroupID.name: cssGroupID
cssGroupID.description: The hub identifier of unit in a stack.

cssGroupType.name: cssGroupType
cssGroupType.description: The model type of the hub unit

cssGroupBoardRevision.name: cssGroupBoardRevision
cssGroupBoardRevision.description: Hardware version of the repeater board.

cssGroupAgentBootVersion.name: cssGroupAgentBootVersion
cssGroupAgentBootVersion.description: Returns the version number of the dual-speed hub BOOT software residing in flash. The format is 'V1.2.3'.

cssGroupAgentFirmwareVersion.name: cssGroupAgentFirmwareVersion
cssGroupAgentFirmwareVersion.description: Returns the version number of the dual-speed hub firmware residing in flash. The format is 'V1.2.3'.

cssGroupAgentStatus.name: cssGroupAgentStatus
cssGroupAgentStatus.description: Status of this hub agent. Each stack allows only one SNMP primary agent. notPresent(1): The hub does not have an agent. primary(2): The agent of this hub is a primary agent. backup(3) : The agent of this hub is a backup agent.

cssGroupAgentPhysAddress.name: cssGroupAgentPhysAddress
cssGroupAgentPhysAddress.description: MAC address of this hub's agent

cssGroupInternalPowerState.name: cssGroupInternalPowerState
cssGroupInternalPowerState.description: Indicates the state of the internal power supply. off : The internal power supply is off. on : The internal power supply is on.

cssGroupRedundantPowerState.name: cssGroupRedundantPowerState
cssGroupRedundantPowerState.description: Indicates the state of the external/backup power supply. off : the switch is not connected to a redundant power source. healthy : a redundant power source is connected to the switch and the power source is operating correctly. faulty : a redundant power source is connected to the switch but a failure exists in the power system.

cssGroupReset.name: cssGroupReset
cssGroupReset.description: Setting this object to reset(2) causes a complete reset of both hardware and software, but does not run the POST (Power On Self Test). Setting this object to noReset(1) has no effect. The switch always returns the value noReset(1) when this object is read.

cssGroupConfigDefaultReset.name: cssGroupConfigDefaultReset
cssGroupConfigDefaultReset.description: Setting this object to reset(2) causes a complete reset of both hardware and software, but does not run the POST (Power On Self Test). All configuration parameters will revert to their factory default settings. Setting this object to noReset(1) has no effect. The switch always returns the value noReset(1) when this object is read.

cssGroupIsolatedState.name: cssGroupIsolatedState
cssGroupIsolatedState.description: Setting this object to isolated(1) causes this hub to be isolated from the back plane bus. Setting this object to attached(2) causes this hub to be attached to the back plane bus.

cssRepeaterPortTable.name: cssRepeaterPortTable
cssRepeaterPortTable.description: The list of repeater port configurations on each hub unit.

cssRepeaterPortEntry.name: cssRepeaterPortEntry
cssRepeaterPortEntry.description: Configuration parameters for an individual repeater port on a hub. The value of rptrPortIndex also indicates the physical port number of the port in the hub. An entry is created for each repeater port in a hub when the hub is connected to the stack. The corresponding entries are removed when the hub is removed from the stack.

cssRepeaterPortName.name: cssRepeaterPortName
cssRepeaterPortName.description: A descriptive string of up to 20 characters used by the network administrator to name a port.

cssRepeaterPortControllerRevision.name: cssRepeaterPortControllerRevision
cssRepeaterPortControllerRevision.description: Returns the revision number of the port controller.

cssRepeaterPortSpeedAdmin.name: cssRepeaterPortSpeedAdmin
cssRepeaterPortSpeedAdmin.description: Set to tenMbps(1) to operate in 10Mbps speed mode. Set to oneHundredMbps(2) to operate in 100Mbps speed mode. Set to autoNegotiate(3) to allow the switch to negotiate with the other end of the connection. The actual operating speed of the port is given by cssRepeaterPortSpeedStatus.

cssRepeaterPortSpeedStatus.name: cssRepeaterPortSpeedStatus
cssRepeaterPortSpeedStatus.description: The operating speed of the port.

cssSwitchPortTable.name: cssSwitchPortTable
cssSwitchPortTable.description: A list of switched ports on extension module on a each hub unit in the stack.

cssSwitchPortEntry.name: cssSwitchPortEntry
cssSwitchPortEntry.description: Configuration parameters for an individual switch module port. An entry is created for each switch port on a module is inserted into a hub in the stack. The corresponding entries are removed when the module is removed from the hub in the stack, or if the hub is removed from the stack.

cssSwitchPortModuleID.name: cssSwitchPortModuleID
cssSwitchPortModuleID.description: Unique ID number of a module unit in a hub as used in the command line interface.

cssSwitchPortPortID.name: cssSwitchPortPortID
cssSwitchPortPortID.description: The unique ID identifying a port on an extension module on a hub as used in the command line interface.

cssSwitchPortName.name: cssSwitchPortName
cssSwitchPortName.description: A descriptive string of up to 20 characters used by the network administrator to name a switch port.

cssSwitchPortType.name: cssSwitchPortType
cssSwitchPortType.description: Type of switch module in this hub.

cssSwitchPortControllerRevision.name: cssSwitchPortControllerRevision
cssSwitchPortControllerRevision.description: The revision number of the port controller.

cssSwitchPortState.name: cssSwitchPortState
cssSwitchPortState.description: Setting this object to enabled(1) enables the port. Setting this object to disabled(2) disables the port.

cssSwitchPortDuplexAdmin.name: cssSwitchPortDuplexAdmin
cssSwitchPortDuplexAdmin.description: Set to fullDuplex(1) to operate in full duplex mode: port will allow simultaneous transmit and receive which can double its bandwidth. Set to halfDuplex(2) to operate in normal mode. Set to autoNegotiate(3) to allow the switch to negotiate the duplex status with the other end of the connection.

cssSwitchPortDuplexStatus.name: cssSwitchPortDuplexStatus
cssSwitchPortDuplexStatus.description: The operating duplex mode of the switched port.

cssSwitchPortSpeedAdmin.name: cssSwitchPortSpeedAdmin
cssSwitchPortSpeedAdmin.description: Set to tenMbps(1) to operate in 10Mbps speed mode. Set to oneHundredMbps(2) to operate in 100Mbps speed mode. Set to autoNegotiate(3) to allow the switch to negotiate the operating speed with the other end of the connection. If the value of object cssSwitchPortType is WS-X4002(2), this object will be read-only, because FX module only supports 100Mbps speed.

cssSwitchPortSpeedStatus.name: cssSwitchPortSpeedStatus
cssSwitchPortSpeedStatus.description: The operating speed of the switched port.

cssSwitchPortLinkStatus.name: cssSwitchPortLinkStatus
cssSwitchPortLinkStatus.description: Indicates the link STATUS of switch port.

ciscoSibuStackableDualSpeedHubRptrPortLi.name: ciscoSibuStackableDualSpeedHubRptrPortLinkChange
ciscoSibuStackableDualSpeedHubRptrPortLi.description: This trap is generated whenever the value of cssRepeaterPortLinkStatus changes for a repeater port.

ciscoSibuStackableDualSpeedHubSwitchPort.name: ciscoSibuStackableDualSpeedHubSwitchPortLinkChange
ciscoSibuStackableDualSpeedHubSwitchPort.description: This trap is generated whenever the value of cssSwitchPortLinkStatus changes for a switch port on an extension module.

ciscoSibuStackableDualSpeedHubCompliance.name: ciscoSibuStackableDualSpeedHubCompliance
ciscoSibuStackableDualSpeedHubCompliance.description: The compliance statement for the Cisco Stackable Dual-Speed Hub products.

ciscoSibuStackableDualSpeedHubGroup.name: ciscoSibuStackableDualSpeedHubGroup
ciscoSibuStackableDualSpeedHubGroup.description: A collection of group objects for use with the Cisco Stackable Dual-Speed Hub products.

ciscoSibuStackableDualSpeedHubRepeaterPo.name: ciscoSibuStackableDualSpeedHubRepeaterPortGroup
ciscoSibuStackableDualSpeedHubRepeaterPo.description: A collection of repeater port objects for use with the Cisco Stackable Dual-Speed Hub products.

ciscoSibuStackableDualSpeedHubSwitchPort.name: ciscoSibuStackableDualSpeedHubSwitchPortGroup
ciscoSibuStackableDualSpeedHubSwitchPort.description: A collection of switch module port objects for use with the Cisco Stackable Dual-Speed Hub products.
